Compiling:
    Typing 'make' will compile the netclasses framework. 

	On OSX, you must have gnustep-make installed to compile!
 
Installing:
	Typing 'make install' as root will install the netclasses framework.

	On OSX, you probably want 'GNUSTEP_INSTALLATION_DIR=/ make install'
	to have it install into /Library

Documentation:
    Documentation/ holds the netclasses documentation.  To make html
    files out of it, simply type 'make'

Use:
	Simply link to the framework after it is installed in your application.
	See the Examples/ directory for examples of the use of netclasses.

